- Groups incoming documents based on the value of a specified expression, 
    then computes the count of documents in each distinct group and sort by it in descending order

- Each output document contains two fields: an _id field containing the distinct 
    grouping value, and a count field containing the number of documents belonging to 
    that grouping or category.

- { $sortByCount:  <expression> } You can specify any expression except for a document literal.